    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix cross-layer parameter mismatch in phy_free_nr_gNB function\n\n### Summary\nThere is a cross-layer parameter mismatch between PHY, MAC, and RRC causing inconsistent operation downstream of function phy_free_nr_gNB. The issue occurs when the phy_init_nr_gNB function exits early due to assertion failures, leaving uninitialized values in max_nb_* fields. When phy_free_nr_gNB is later called, it uses these garbage values as loop bounds, leading to undefined behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/nr_init.c`: Added initialization of max_nb_pucch, max_nb_srs, max_nb_pdsch, and max_nb_pusch to safe default values (1) at the beginning of phy_init_nr_gNB function to prevent cross-layer parameter mismatch in case of early exit.\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue can be observed when:\n1. phy_init_nr_gNB is called but exits early due to assertion failures (e.g., invalid Ptx/Prx values)\n2. phy_free_nr_gNB is subsequently called\n3. The function attempts to loop through arrays using uninitialized max_nb_* values\n4. This results in either accessing invalid memory addresses or not properly freeing allocated memory\n\nSymptoms include segmentation faults, memory leaks, or corrupted memory during gNB cleanup operations.\n"
}